<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTI-466 A and B Series DT/DTI/DTA-466 C Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1993) - ENGINE DIAGNOSTIC TOOLS -
        DESIGN TECHNOLOGY "TECH TIME" Model 3354 Dynamic Timing Meter - TIMING LIGHT METHOD - CRANKSHAFT MONITORING
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TIMING LIGHT METHOD - CRANKSHAFT MONITORING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the timing light
                <emph type="bold">(10, Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e450_39.xml" xrefid="ef4500411">4.11</hotlnk>)
                </emph>
                to the timing light socket
                <emph type="bold">(2, Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e450_39.xml" xrefid="ef4500411">4.11</hotlnk>).
                </emph>
                Turn the function switch
                <emph type="bold">(1, Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e450_39.xml" xrefid="ef4500411">4.11</hotlnk>)
                </emph>
                to the
                <emph type="bold">"LIGHT"</emph>
                position. Display will show
                <emph type="bold">"RPM... 0, DEGREES... 0.0"</emph>
                if the
                <emph type="bold">"TIMING LIGHT"</emph>
                mode is selected.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set timing unit to
                <emph type="bold">"LOW TRIGGER"</emph>
                mode.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start the engine and allow it to reach operaing temperature. A steady RPM reading should be
                observed.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>An erratic reading may indicate the pick-up needs to be retightened or repositioned.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check initial dynamic timing and advance by adjusting the engine RPM as directed in Section
                5.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Aim the timing light at the timing marks on the vibration damper. Depress the trigger and
                depress the
                <emph type="bold">"ADJUST" "&#8593;" or'&#8595;"'</emph>
                buttons
                <emph type="bold">(5, Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e450_39.xml" xrefid="ef4500411">4.11</hotlnk>).
                </emph>
                Press"&#8593;" to move the
                <emph type="bold">"TDC"</emph>
                mark counterclockwise or "&#8595;" to move the
                <emph type="bold">"TDC"</emph>
                mark clockwise.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When the pointer and the
                <emph type="bold">"TDC"</emph>
                mark are aligned, observe the reading on the
                <emph type="bold">"DEGREE"</emph>display -- this will be the exact number of degrees off
                <emph type="bold">"TDC"</emph>
                at which fuel injection occurs.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repaint the scraped fuel line when timing operation is complete, to protect the line against
                corrosion.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
